main event: A civilian reported seeing one unidentified object flying west to east over Houma, Louisiana for 10 minutes on December 7, 1966.
interesting points: The object was described as cigar-shaped, white and orange in color with a green tail.
The witness, a 25-year-old man, observed the object from 29 to 90 degrees in the southwestern sky.
The report mentions potential tug boat lights reflecting on the water as a possible explanation, but no radar contacts were made at the time of the sighting.
The Air Force's conclusion was that there was 'insufficient data' to evaluate the sighting.
The Air Force requested additional details from the witness to further investigate the sighting.
sighted object: cigar-shaped object, white and orange in color with a green tail
